Yeah, that would work! You could even use the `type` argument to `sse.publish()` so that keep-alive messages are their own type. That way, you could publishing your meaningful messages as a separate type, and code up your Javascript to only pay attention to messages of the meaningful type. As an example:

```python
@celery.task                                                                                                  
def publish_keep_alive():                                                                                     
    sse.publish({'message': 'keep alive'}, type='keepalive')

@app.route('/test')
def testing():
    sse.publish({'value': 42}, type='data')
```
